{%- comment -%}
  main-work.liquid — body content for the Work page.
  Edit this file to update the page. No section editor in admin.
  SEO + JSON-LD live in snippets/seo-meta.liquid (context-aware via page.handle).
{%- endcomment -%}

<header class="hero short">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Work · Three businesses · Ten years</span>
      <h1>The work we sell is the work <em>we do every day.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">The case studies are the businesses we've built. Three brands. Hundreds of thousands of customers. The operating playbook we sell is the one we run every day on these.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ============ STIX GOLF ============ -->
  <section class="section" id="stix">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">Case 01 · Stix Golf</span>
        <h2>Direct-to-consumer golf clubs.<br/><em>$100M+ in lifetime sales.<br/>Series A &amp; B.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="row-2col asym">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">DTC · Premium · 2020–present</span>
          <div style="margin-top:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;">
            <span class="tag">CRO · Compete tier · Perform tier</span>
            <span class="tag">Triple Whale · Windsor · Klaviyo · Gorgias</span>
            <span class="tag">11k+ post-purchase responses</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>Stix sells direct-to-consumer golf clubs at a quarter the price of legacy brands without the legacy-brand intimidation. Founded 2020. Took it from zero to $8M in year one, through Series A, then Series B. Over $100M in lifetime sales and hundreds of thousands of customers.</p>

          <p style="margin-top:24px;"><strong>What we built that LF now sells:</strong></p>
          <ul style="margin:14px 0 0 0;list-style:none;padding:0;">
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The CRO testing framework: 10 parallel slots, progressive traffic allocation, metafield-driven runtime config. Validated at scale.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The intimidation framework — four cohorts mapped to four psychological barriers, validated by 11k post-purchase survey responses.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The Triple Whale REST integration that replaced Moby (which was returning numbers 2-3x off ground truth in April 2026).</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The Daily Sales Plan as forecast source-of-truth — pacing reports anchor to plan-base, not rolling-baseline.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> Comment marketing at scale — running every two hours across IG, TikTok, YouTube, with hard 15-minute budgets and skip-on-failure resilience.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats" style="margin-top:80px;">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="label">Lifetime sales</div>
          <div class="val">$100M+</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="label">Funding stages</div>
          <div class="val">Series A &amp; B</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="label">Customers</div>
          <div class="val">100K+<span class="small">Hundreds of thousands</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ HOST MODERN ============ -->
  <section class="section rule" id="hostmodern">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">Case 02 · Host Modern</span>
        <h2>Heated serving dishes.<br/><em>$4.5M Year 1.<br/>10%+ profit margin.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="row-2col asym">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">DTC · Kitchen · 2024–present</span>
          <div style="margin-top:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;">
            <span class="tag">~20 production skills</span>
            <span class="tag">Wiki · Notion · Triple Whale</span>
            <span class="tag">7 seasonal campaign packs</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>Host Modern sells the first heated serving dish that keeps food at temperature for hours without a power outlet. Launched in 2024. $4.5M in year-one revenue with a 10%+ profit margin. Gabe is the CEO.</p>

          <p style="margin-top:24px;"><strong>What we built that LF now sells:</strong></p>
          <ul style="margin:14px 0 0 0;list-style:none;padding:0;">
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The full AI skill library template — about 20 production skills covering media buying, comment marketing, comment engagement, marketing analysis, FP&A, demand planning, SEO, content repurposing.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The Notion Approval Queue + Run Log + Skill Registry hub — central inbox for proposals, ledger of what ran, source of truth for what's installed.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The 7-rule data validation library — the "Step 0" that runs before every media-buyer decision. Caught the April 24th UTC timezone bug that would have inverted a ROAS read by 81%.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The brand foundation trio: brand context, copy rules, design system. Each enforced through tooling, not just documented.</li>
            <li style="position:relative;padding-left:18px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);"><span style="position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--lf-ember);">—</span> The Wiki + tokens.css system — every polished HTML view for the team has a home, all share one design source of truth.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats" style="margin-top:80px;">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="label">Year 1 revenue</div>
          <div class="val">$4.5M</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="label">Status</div>
          <div class="val">10%+ <span class="small">profit margin</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="label">Production skills</div>
          <div class="val">~20</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ INFLUENCE MOBILE ============ -->
  <section class="section rule" id="influence">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">Case 03 · Influence Mobile</span>
        <h2>Mobile ad network.<br/><em>$65M revenue.<br/>100M+ app installs.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="row-2col asym">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Adtech · Mobile · 2014–2022</span>
          <div style="margin-top:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;">
            <span class="tag">#3 mobile ad network in the world</span>
            <span class="tag">Real-time bidding · attribution</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>Gabe co-founded Influence Mobile and helped grow it into the third-largest mobile ad network in the world by revenue. $200M+ in lifetime revenue. 100M+ app installs delivered. The business taught the operating fundamentals — attribution under noise, fraud detection, real-time decisioning, and what it actually takes to keep complex automated systems running in production without human-in-the-loop interventions.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:18px;">The technical instincts that make LF skills resilient — hard time budgets, skip-on-failure isolation, log everything, no per-item AI calls when batch will do — come from this work. AI consulting is in many ways adtech with better tools.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ NEXT CASE STUDIES ============ -->
  <section class="section sm rule">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">Up next</span>
        <h2>Client case studies <em>arrive in 2026.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="row-2col asym">
        <div>
          <p style="font-family:var(--lf-serif);font-style:italic;font-weight:350;font-size:18px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--lf-graphite);">
            We'd rather show you our own businesses than dress up an early client engagement.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>The Suncast Stack-Up DTC engagement is in flight. Other engagements are in early stages. We'll publish the case studies once we have results worth publishing — no logo wall before the work.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:24px;"><a class="inline-link" href="{{ routes.root_url }}pages/contact">Talk to us about being one of the early case studies →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CTA ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-block dark">
        <h2>Operator credibility is the work.<br/><em>The first call is free.</em></h2>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn ember" href="{{ routes.root_url }}pages/contact">Book a call</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

